  <!-- About -->
  <section id="about">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="section-label">About Us</p>
      <div class="section-title">THE FOUNDERS</div>
      <div class="founders-intro">
        <p>Two operators with complementary superpowers — one who has built and run the technology, one who has built and run the revenue engine. Together they've worked at companies that shaped the enterprise computing landscape over three decades.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="founders-grid">

        <!-- Brock -->
        <div class="founder-card fade-up">
          <div class="founder-name">BROCK MOWRY</div>
          <div class="founder-title">Co-Founder &nbsp;·&nbsp; Technology & Infrastructure</div>
          <p class="founder-bio">
            Brock is a technology executive and Chief Technology Officer with a career built on designing and operating infrastructure that others consider complex. He started hands-on — building networks, deploying ERP systems, migrating exchange environments — and scaled all the way to CTO shaping product roadmaps at Tintri, one of the leading enterprise storage and cloud companies.
          </p>
          <p class="founder-bio">
            He co-founded WHOA.com and architected a multi-tenant cloud hosting platform from the ground up, leading a distributed engineering team through acquisitions, customer migrations, and ISO 27001 compliance. At Diamanti he led systems engineering for Kubernetes-native infrastructure before becoming Field CTO and then CTO at Tintri where he holds a patent in cloud-based threat observation systems.
          </p>
          <p class="founder-bio">
            His expertise spans cloud architecture, Kubernetes, hybrid cloud, ransomware defense, enterprise data platforms, Cisco UCS, NetApp, EMC, and multi-tenant operations. He is a recognized thought leader and frequent speaker at industry conferences and webinars.
          </p>
